rComments: Very straight forward.  Listen and take good notes, ask questions and you'll do fine.

Pitard is great, but for each set of religions there is a different professor lecturing. Some were great, but a few were HORRIBLE, and very hard to comprehend. My TA was really bad too. But it wasn't that hard and counts for either Western or NonWestern gen ed. So it's worth it. Just be sure to make sure which lecturers dont put lectures online
